                                         "text":  "<p><h3>Incas (Tawantinsuyu)</h3>The image in this section shows the territory of the Inca Empire (<i>Tawantinsuyu</i>) overlaid on present-day South America, illustrating its extent before the arrival of colonizers in <htdate0>",
                                         "source":  [
                                                        {
                                                            "type":  1,
                                                            "uuid":  "ed31f80e-ddd3-448a-9331-a0b6ac5f82fd",
                                                            "text":  "Hechler, R. S.",
                                                            "page":  "",
                                                            "date_time":  {
                                                                              "type":  "gregory",
                                                                              "year":  "2022",
                                                                              "month":  "",
                                                                              "day":  ""
                                                                          }
                                                        }
                                                    ],
                                         "date_time":  null,
                                         "isTable":  false,
                                         "imgdesc":  "",
                                         "format":  "html",
                                         "PostMention":  "."
                                     },
                                     {
                                         "text":  "The study of the Inca Empire (<i>Tawantinsuyu</i>) like other scientific fields, is constantly evolving. Chronicles and research related to the empire indicate a general consensus about the lineage of Viracocha's descendants; however, it’s possible that some kings (<i>Sapa</i>) remain undocumented. Additionally, recent research challenges the traditional view of rapid territorial expansion, suggesting that this conclusion may be inaccurate",
                                         "source":  [
